## How to Invoke Workflows in Cursor

When the user mentions a workflow, read the corresponding file from `.cursor/workflows/` and follow it step-by-step.

### Workflow Commands

| User Says | Read This File | Purpose |
|-----------|----------------|---------|
| "Create PRD using prd-creation-workflow" | `.cursor/workflows/prd-creation-workflow.md` | Define WHAT & WHY |
| "Create TDD using tdd-creation-workflow" | `.cursor/workflows/tdd-creation-workflow.md` | Design HOW |
| "Break down using task-breakdown-workflow" | `.cursor/workflows/task-breakdown-workflow.md` | Create TICKETS |
| "Implement ticket [ID] using linear-ticket-workflow" | `.cursor/workflows/linear-ticket-workflow.md` | Build FEATURE |

### How to Reference Files in Cursor

Use `@filename` syntax to reference workflow files:
- `@.cursor/workflows/prd-creation-workflow.md`
- `@.cursor/workflows/tdd-creation-workflow.md`
- `@.cursor/reference/quick-reference.md`

### Quick Reference

For cheat sheet, reference: `@.cursor/reference/quick-reference.md`

